newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet fuel up with futures, demand thin.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet fuel up with futures, demand thin.

text.p: NWE jet fuel was slightly stronger on Monday in line with futures, but traders said both the barge and the cargo markets were very quiet.

Barges premiums were put at Oct IPE +$28/+$30 fob ARA. On the cargo market, traders said supply continued to be tight but this was countered by thin demand. Cif cargo premiums were assessed at Oct IPE +$36/+$37.
Traders said buyers appeared to have covered their requirements for September and that current backwardation on the IPE futures market was also acting as a deterrent to buy.
